<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="come-vi">come <strong><em>vi</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kʌm/    美 /kʌm/  </p>
<p>(came, come)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>来；来到；到来：</strong></h4>
<p>反 go </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The National Day is coming soon.
国庆节很快就要到了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The lovely pupils <strong>came running</strong> to meet their teacher. 
可爱的小学生们跑来迎接他们的老师。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>达到；处于 (某一位置或状态)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>came last</strong> in the competition.
这次比赛我排最后一名。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come to / into</strong>:
</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come into sight / view</strong>
进入视线；被看见</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come to</strong> an end / <strong>a stop</strong>
结束/停止</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come to a decision / conclusion / agreement</strong>
作出决定/得出结论/达成协议</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the 1990s the shawls came into fashion among rich people.
20世纪90年代，披巾在富人中流行起来。</p><footer>外研⑤ – 6</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>变为；变成：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>come + adj</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>May all your dreams <strong>come true</strong>!
祝你们梦想成真！</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>渐渐开始：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>come to do sth</strong>:
</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Now I am in college, and have come to realize how important it is to read fiction.
我现在在上大学，开始认识到读小说是多么重要。</p><footer>2010 四川</footer></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>(货物、产品等) 有生产；有供应：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Bicycles come in different colors — silver, green, red, blue, yellow, whatever you want.
有各种颜色的自行车——银色、绿色、蓝色、黄色，你想要什么颜色的都有。</p><footer>2013 辽宁改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When do strawberries <strong>come in</strong>?
草莓什么时候上市？</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="come-about">come about</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(尤指未经计划地) 发生；产生：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please tell me how the accident came about.
请告诉我事故是怎么发生的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The flood came about as a result of the heavy rain.
大雨引发了洪水。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-across">come across</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>偶然遇到；碰见 (meet)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When reading articles related to science, we often come across difficult or unfamiliar words.
读与科学相关的文章时，我们常常碰到难词或生词。</p><footer>译林⑤ – 3</footer></div>

<p>2.<strong>被理解：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He spoke for a long time, but his meaning did not come across.
他讲了很久，但还是没有把意思讲明白。</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>给人以…印象 (come over)</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He came across as a sympathetic person.
他给人的印象是一个富有同情心的人。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-along">come along</h3>
<p>1.<strong>一起来；出现；（非正式用语）进展：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Are you sure you really want all our friends to come along?
你确定你真想让我们的朋友都一起来吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When the right opportunity comes along, take it.
好机会出现时要抓住它。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The patient is coming along well after the operation.
手术后病人的状况良好。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-and-go">come and go</h3>
<p>1.<strong>来来去去；时有时无</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="come-around-round">come around / round</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>拜访；探访 (come over)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Come around when you have time.
有空时过来玩吧。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>发生；降临：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>With the summer vacation coming around, some students begin to make plans for it.
随着暑假的到来，一些学生开始为之做打算。</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>改变观点：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It took him a while to come around to the idea.
他过了一会才改变观点，接受这个主意。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-back">come back</h3>
<p>1.<strong>回来 (return)；再度流行：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Long skirts have been out of fashion for a long time, but they are coming back. 
长裙已经过时很长时间，但又要流行起来。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-by">come by</h3>
<p>1.<strong>顺路看望；获得 (稀有或很难得到的事物)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She said she’d come by later. 
她说晚些时候再过来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jobs are hard to come by these days.
如今找工作很难。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-down">come down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>下来；下降；倒塌：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>House prices are coming down soon. 
房价很快就要降了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That old building came down on a rainy morning.
那座老楼房在一个雨天的早晨倒塌了。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-down-to">come down to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>归结为；传到…手里：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Their quarrel comes down to money. 
他们吵架说到底是因为钱。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The custom has come down to us from our old generations.
这个习俗是从祖辈传下来的。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-from">come from</h3>
<p>1.<strong>出生于；来自；产自；源自于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My success came from good planning and better doing combined.
我的成功源自良好的计划和更好的行动相结合。</p><footer>2016 浙江书面表达改</footer></div>

<h3 id="come-in">come in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>到达；被收到；取得 (名次)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What time does your train come in? 
你的那趟火车什么时候到达？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His horse came in second. 
他的马跑了第二名。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-off">come off</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>(从…) 离开：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>come off work
下班</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>People coming off a busy spring and summer have a moment of relaxation.
人们度过了繁忙的春夏，有了片刻的清闲。</p><footer>2011 福建</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>脱落；掉下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A wheel had come off.
车轮脱落了。</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>结果是；成为：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you check your e-mail while on the phone with a friend, you may come off as absent-minded.
如果在跟朋友通电话时查看电子邮件，你可能会显得心不在焉。</p><footer>2010 浙江改</footer></div>

<h3 id="come-on">come on</h3>
<p>1.<strong>快点；进展；算了吧：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Come on! We don’t have much time.
快点！我们时间不多了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The knee’s coming on fine; I’m walking comfortably already.
我的膝盖恢复得很好，现在走路已经不疼了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Oh, come on — you know that isn’t true!
哦，得了吧——你知道那不是真的！</p></div>

<h3 id="come-out">come out</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>出来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The rain stopped and the sun came out.
雨停了，太阳出来了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The neighbors <strong>came out of</strong> their houses to see if we had a gas leak.
邻居们走出家门看我们家是否发生了煤气泄漏。</p><footer>2015 四川</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>出版；发行；面市：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My first novel came out while I was at college.
我在上大学时出版了我的第一部小说。</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>显现；结果是；（照片）清楚地冲洗出来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let me know how the voting comes out.
告诉我投票结果。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It came out that</strong> some government officials received money from the company.
真相是一些政府官员收了那家公司的钱。</p><footer>北师大⑦ – 20</footer></div>

<h3 id="come-over">come over</h3>
<p>1.<strong>来访；拜访 (come around)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My aunt came over for a visit yesterday.
昨天我姑姑来访。</p></div>

<p>2.<strong>(使) 某人突然感觉到：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I came over all shy whenever I saw her.
无论何时见到她我都很害羞。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A wave of sleepiness came over him.
他突然犯困了。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-to-sb">come to sb</h3>
<p>1.<strong>被某人想到：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The answer came to me in a flash. 
我突然想到了答案。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-up">come up</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>上来；上升 (rise)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Come up! I’m upstairs!
上来！我在楼上！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We watched the sun come up.
我们看着太阳升了起来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I planted some lily seeds in the yard. But they failed to come up.
我在院子里种了些百合花种子，但它们没有发芽。</p><footer>2012 重庆</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>走近；靠近：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>came up to</strong> me and asked me the way to the station.
他走近我，问我去车站的路怎么走。</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>被提出；被提及 (arise)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The “air pollution” topic comes up every year.
空气污染这个话题每年都会被提及。</p></div>

<p>4.★ <strong>发生；即将到来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m afraid I can’t go — something’s come up.
恐怕我不能去了——出了点事情。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Danny, I heard your birthday is coming up.
丹尼，我听说你的生日快到了。</p></div>

<h3 id="come-up-with">come up with</h3>
<p>1.<strong>想出；提出；提供：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Our class came up with the idea to make better use of used materials.
我们班的同学提出了这一想法，以更好利用废旧材料。</p><footer>2016 北京书面表达</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They want to buy the house, but they couldn’t come up with the cash.
他们想买房，但是拿不出这笔现金。</p></div>

<h3 id="to-come">to come</h3>
<p>1.<strong>将来；未来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When you sleep, your body prepares you for the day to come.
在睡眠时，你的身体在为迎接新的一天做着准备。</p><footer>译林① – 3</footer></div>

<h3 id="when-it-comes-to-doing-sth">when it comes to (doing) sth</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在某方面；说到 (做) 某事：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Both groups scored similarly when it came to memorizing facts. 
在记忆事实方面两组得分差不多。</p><footer>2014 辽宁</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When it comes to friends, I desire those who will share my happiness. 
说到朋友，我渴望那些会分享我的快乐的人。</p><footer>2008 北京</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— You know what? I’ve got a New Year concert ticket.
— Oh,  <strong><em>_</em></strong>You’re kidding.   （2018 江苏）<br />
A.so what?<br />
B.go ahead.<br />
C.come on.<br />
D.what for?  </li>
<li>— Hi, Dr Brown! I’m a little early. Should I wait outside?
— No. <strong><em>_</em></strong>.  （2015 福建）<br />
A.That’s right<br />
B.My pleasure<br />
C.Come on in<br />
D.Take it easy  </li>
<li>Is this your necklace, Mary? I came <strong><em>_</em></strong> it when I was cleaning the bathroom this morning.  （2014 湖北改）  </li>
<li>Would you like to come <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ with us to the film tonight?  （2013 全国改）  </li>
<li>— Have you come up <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ some new ideas?
— Yeah. I’ll tell you later.  （2007 江苏改）  </li>
<li>— Four dollars a pair? I think it’s a bit too much.
— If you buy three pairs, the price for each will come <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ to three fifty.  （2006 安徽改）  </li>
<li>It’s already 10 o’clock. I wonder how it came <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ that she was two hours late on such a short trip.  （2006 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. C  2. C  3. across  4. along  5.  with  6. down  7. about  </p></div>